The paper deals with the problem of estimating a signal from its noisy linear random Gaussian projections, which is a problem relevant in compressed sensing, sparse superposition codes, and code division multiple access. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also uses statistical physics and state evolution analysis, which are relevant to the Mathematical Physics (cs.MP) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. However, since the focus of the paper is on the mutual information in random linear estimation, the Information Theory and Signal Processing sub-categories are the most likely.
